    "note": "Pado's fluorophore is Super Ecliptic pHluorin A227D (SE227D) — the same FP first reported in ArcLight (Methods; also used in Marina). Super ecliptic pHluorin carries the S65T (EGFP) mutation, which collapses its excitation to a single ~488 nm peak, making it spectrally near-identical to EGFP; no measured super ecliptic pHluorin ex/em curve is published, so the FPbase EGFP excitation/emission curve is used as a near-exact representation (peaks 488/511, including EGFP's ~0.17 shoulder at 400 nm). The stored arrays were already the verbatim FPbase EGFP curve (corr 1.0, max diff 0.0 vs the EGFP curve) but carried no source attribution; this change only adds the missing citation.",
    "proofread": false,
    "source": "FPbase: EGFP",
    "sourceFigure": "FPbase"
  },
