    "source": "doi:10.1038/srep23865",
    "sourceImage": "/fv-sources/pado.jpg",
    "sourceFigure": "Fig. 2a",
    "proofread": false,
    "note": "Fig. 2a is a representative single-trial trace whose voltage command has only two depolarizing step levels from the -70 mV holding potential: +30 mV (a 100-mV step, <5% ΔF/F) and +130 mV (a 200-mV step, ~10% ΔF/F). ΔF/F read from those step deflections and normalized to 0 at -70 mV. Removed two fabricated/interpolated points (-20 mV at -1.5%, +80 mV at -6%) that correspond to no step in the figure. The paper reports no hyperpolarized or finer-grained F-V data; the +130 mV signal is partly confounded by a pH-dependent baseline jump from Hv channel activation."
  },
  "kinetics": [
    {
      "on": 93,
      "off": 10,
      "temperature": "35°C",
      "note": "τon and τoff of the optical signal for a 200-mV depolarizing step in HEK293 cells, read from the Fig. 5b bar graph (n=7, pH 7.4 / 100 mM HEPES standard condition): τon ≈ 93 ms, τoff ≈ 10 ms — Pado is a slow sensor. Single time-constant fits (no multi-exponential reported). Raising external pH to 7.8 speeds τon to ~36 ms with little effect on τoff (~9 ms). Recorded at 35°C. Previously stored τon=30 ms, which matched the pH 7.8 condition rather than the standard pH 7.4.",
